# Copy to `.env` and fill with values from Supabase → Project Settings → API.
# Restart Expo (`npx expo start --clear`) after changing env.
#
# The anon key is designed for client apps (protected by Row Level Security).
#
# Wardrobe + outfits + wardrobe photos + Discover: run SQL in `supabase/migrations/`
# (wardrobe_items, outfits, wardrobe_images_storage, published_outfits,
# published_outfits_author_delete, published_outfit_likes, wardrobe_image_refs,
# profiles, user_follows, following_feed_rpc (20260329190500), published_outfit_comments,
# user_activity, 20260329220000_user_activity_read_at) in the Supabase SQL Editor (and enable Email auth under Authentication → Providers).
#
# Wardrobe derivatives: deploy Edge Function `process-wardrobe-image`
# (`supabase/functions/process-wardrobe-image`) — see summary in repo deliverable notes.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
